     <blockquote><p>"No one can read this book and not have his thoughts and conscience provoked…It is a profound and passionate effort toward healing a major schism that is long overdue." </p>
<p>– <b><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lawrence_Reed" rel="nofollow">Lawrence W. Reed</a></b>, President, <a href="http://www.fee.org/" rel="nofollow">Foundation for Economic Education.</a> and author of <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Republic-If-We-Can-Keep-ebook/dp/B007WU6HTE" rel="nofollow">A Republic, If We Can Keep It</a>.</p></blockquote>
